    <note type="dates"><date>1815–56</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish merchant and botanist. Partner in the merchant house William Gourlie &amp; Son, 8 South Frederick Street, Glasgow. Collected mosses, shells, and fossil plants. An active member of the Glasgow Philosophical Society; local secretary in Glasgow for the Botanical Society of Edinburgh. A local secretary for the British Association for the Advancement of Science meeting in Glasgow in 1855.</p></note>
